thread.title: That New York Condo Just Got a Lot More Expensive

author: Josh Barbanel
title: That New York Condo Just Got a Lot More Expensive
text:
Apartment shoppers in Manhattan are taking a pause after a federal tax overhaul removed some key incentives for homeownership, brokers say.
After four consecutive months of increases, the number of contracts signed in December declined both for new condo buildings and older co-ops and condos.
